body_html: Looking at the code of that notebook, I think the "No scalar data was found" error message is expected behavior: the notebook doesn't explicitly log anything to the summary_writer, apart from sess.graph_def (which probably accounts for the 8kb of data in the event log file). If you click on the "Graph" link at the top of the TensorBoard page, you should be able to see the graph visualization, as described in the notebook.

body: Looking at the code of that notebook, I think the "No scalar data was found" error message is expected behavior: the notebook doesn't explicitly log anything to the `summary_writer`, apart from `sess.graph_def` (which probably accounts for the 8kb of data in the event log file). If you click on the "Graph" link at the top of the TensorBoard page, you should be able to see the graph visualization, as described in the notebook.
